Package user.models

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actuator
    An actuator is a connected object managed by the server and performing physical actions according to it.
    ActuatorCategory  
    Ambience  
    AtomicAction
    An action is a message sent by the server to the actuators which needs to react according to it.
    Behaviour  
    Category  
    Command
    A command is the information about the possible values (continuous or discrete) an actuator can receive to perform one action
    CommandValue
    A value is an information the actuator needs to perform an action or modify its state It allows the server to send the right action to the actuators.
    ComplexAction
    A complex action is a collection of atomic actions.
    ContinuousCommandValue
    A continous value is a float which is an information the actuator needs to perform an action or modify its state
    ContinuousValue
    A continuous value is a value which is a decimal number.
    DiscreteCommandValue
    A discrete value is a variable which the current value is a String among possible values.
    DiscreteValue
    A discrete value is a string which is an information the actuator needs to perform an action or modify its state.
    EnvironmentVariable
    An environment variable is an interesting value for the server, related to the environment.
    ExternalActor  
    Right  
    Role  
    Sensor
    A sensor is a connected object in charge of sending useful changes about environment variables to the server.
    SensorCategory  
    User  
    Value
